This paper is about improving neural machine translation (NMT) using deep recurrent models with fast forward connections. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which includes papers on natural language processing and machine translation. The paper also discusses the use of neural networks, which suggests that it could also be categorized as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper mentions the use of attention mechanisms and handling of unknown words, which could also place it in the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) category.
